creator: Thomas Moore
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 12 recordings of Oh! Had We Some Bright Little Isle Of Our Own by Thomas Moore. This was the Weekly Poetry project for August 2, 2015 Read in English by Bruce Kachuk; David Lawrence; Newgatenovelist; Garth Burton; Greg Giordano; Ian King; J. McDougall; Lee Ann Howlett; Larry Wilson; Leonard Wilson; Maria Kasper and SkyAlbatross. Thomas Moore was an Irish poet, singer, songwriter, and entertainer, now best remembered for the lyrics of "The Minstrel Boy" and "The Last Rose of Summer". Moore is often considered Ireland's National Bard and is to Ireland what Robert Burns is to Scotland. ( Wikipedia) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (8MB)
